- Chapter 11: 9. Learning: Listen from the Inside Out
    - what came out: one skill
        - listen-from-the-inside-out: the core shift from "I understand" to "help me understand." Three techniques: inquiry (ask only to learn), paraphrasing (restate to verify and show understanding), acknowledgment (show their view made an impression, without agreeing). Managing the internal voice and the when-you-can't-listen technique are folded in.
    - why: one stance + three implementation techniques. All cohere as one skill.
    - decision: saturated (1 skill)
